                    ]
                }
            ]


## Access Diary [/api/v1/diary/diary_id]            

### Retrieve a single diary entry [GET]

You retrieve a single diary using this action. 
Request contains Authorization token in header

    + Headers

            Authorization: Token

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/diary/diary_id

    + Body

                {
                    "Date Modified": "null",
                    "Date created": "Sun, 22 Jul 2018 13:49:27 GMT",
                    "id": 1,
                    "name": "Rally Uganda"
                }

## Update diary [/api/v1/diary/diary_id]   
### Update a diary entry [PUT]

You update a bucket using this action. 
Request contains Authorization token in header

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: token
        
    + Body

            {
                "name": "The best tour in africa"
            }


+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/diary/diary_id

    + Body

            {
                
                "Info": "Diary successfully modified"
            }

## Delete diary [/api/v1/diary/diary_id] 
### Delete a diary entry [DELETE]

You delete a diary entry using this action. 
Request contains Authorization token in header


    + Headers

            Authorization: token
        

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/diary/diary_id

    + Body

            {
                'Info': 'Diary entry deleted'
            }

## Add Descriptions [/api/v1/diary/1/items]            

### Add diary descriptions to diary entries [POST]

You add a diary description item using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing an description name

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: token
    + Body

            {
                "desc": "Win first rally in Uganda"
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/diary/1/item

    + Body

            {
                'Info': 'Diary description added'
            }

## Modify Description item [/api/v1/diary/1/item/item_id]            

### Edit diary description [PUT]

You may edit a diary description item using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing an description name

+ Request (application/json)


    + Headers

            Authorization: Token
    + Body

            {
                "desc": "Win  all rally's on the calender"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/diary/1/item/1

    + Body

            {
                'Info': 'Diary successfully modified',
            }